OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1774887078
OL,3,CHow could US forces seize Kharg Island
OL,4,Cand would Iran benefit?
OL,6,FWords by ITV News' Lucy L. Middleton
OL,8,FDonald Trump has threatened to
OL,9,F"obliterate" Iran's oil hub, Kharg
OL,10,FIsland, if a deal between the
OL,11,Fcountries is not reached soon.
OL,13,FThe tiny island, which is about 20
OL,14,Fmiles from Iran's southwestern coast,
OL,15,Fis the terminal for nearly all of
OL,16,FIran's oil exports and has remained
OL,17,Factive, generating revenue for the
OL,18,Fregime during the ongoing war.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1774887078
OL,3,CHow could US forces seize Kharg Island
OL,4,Cand would Iran benefit?
OL,6,FThe US bombed the island during the
OL,7,Fsecond week of the war, and on Monday
OL,8,FTrump warned he would "completely
OL,9,Fobliterate" the land, along with
OL,10,FIran's electric generating plants, oil
OL,11,Fwells and "possibly all desalinisation
OL,12,Fplants" if no agreement is made.
OL,14,FThousands of US troops began arriving
OL,15,Fin Iran as the conflict entered its
OL,16,Ffifth week, with Trump seemingly
OL,17,Fweighing up whether or not to "take"
OL,18,FKharg Island, suggesting a land
OL,19,Finvasion has not been ruled out.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1774887078
OL,3,CHow could US forces seize Kharg Island
OL,4,Cand would Iran benefit?
OL,6,FIran has vowed to avenge any attack on
OL,7,Fthe island, with parliamentary speaker
OL,8,FMohammad Bagher Qalibaf stating on
OL,9,FSunday that the country's forces are
OL,10,F"waiting for the arrival of American
OL,11,Ftroops on the ground to set them on
OL,12,Ffire".
OL,14,FITV News takes a closer look at what
OL,15,Fcould unfold.
OL,17,FWhat is the significance of Kharg
OL,18,FIsland?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1774887078
OL,3,CHow could US forces seize Kharg Island
OL,4,Cand would Iran benefit?
OL,6,FKharg Island serves as Iran's primary
OL,7,Foil hub - the terminal for nearly all
OL,8,Fof Iran's oil exports - as it has much
OL,9,Fdeeper water than Iran's coastline,
OL,10,Fmeaning the world's largest tankers
OL,11,Fcan berth there.
OL,13,FIt is Iran's main loading, collection
OL,14,Fand storage point for crude oil, and
OL,15,Fits terminal has remained active
OL,16,Fduring the war, generating revenue for
OL,17,Fthe Islamic Revolutionary Guard Corps
OL,18,F(IRGC).
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1774887078
OL,3,CHow could US forces seize Kharg Island
OL,4,Cand would Iran benefit?
OL,6,FThis means Iran has been able to
OL,7,Fsustain fuel reserves while much of
OL,8,Fthe world struggles with the Strait of
OL,9,FHormuz - a major waterway for oil -
OL,10,Fbeing almost entirely closed by the
OL,11,Fnation.
OL,13,FSeizing Kharg could give the US
OL,14,Fleverage against Iran, as well as
OL,15,Foffering a potential foothold for
OL,16,Fsurveillance or temporary staging,
OL,17,Fallowing troops to monitor Iranian
OL,18,Fmaritime activity.
OL,20,FHow could the US seize the island?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30406
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1774887078
OL,3,CHow could US forces seize Kharg Island
OL,4,Cand would Iran benefit?
OL,6,FThe US Marine Corps could seize Kharg
OL,7,FIsland by ship or from the air,
OL,8,Fmilitary sciences expert Dr Sidharth
OL,9,FKaushal told ITV News, but "several
OL,10,Fpreconditions" would need to be met.
OL,12,FIf it was by sea, threats from Iran's
OL,13,Fcoastal defence cruise missiles would
OL,14,Fneed to be suppressed in order for US
OL,15,Famphibious assault ships (LHAs) - a
OL,16,Ftype of warship - to move into range
OL,17,Fof the island, Kaushal said.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30407
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1774887078
OL,3,CHow could US forces seize Kharg Island
OL,4,Cand would Iran benefit?
OL,6,FMine countermeasures support would
OL,7,Falso be needed if Iran has placed
OL,8,Fmines in the island's approaches,
OL,9,Fwhich they are "likely to do", he
OL,10,Fcontinued.
OL,12,FSubscribe for free to our weekly
OL,13,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,14,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,15,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,17,FIran has already threatened to deploy
OL,18,Fnaval mines across the Persian Gulf if
OL,19,Fthe US or Israel attack its islands.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30408
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1774887078
OL,3,CHow could US forces seize Kharg Island
OL,4,Cand would Iran benefit?
OL,6,F"Even if the Iranians cannot lay a
OL,7,Fhuge number of mines in Hormuz, they
OL,8,Fcan do so on the approaches to their
OL,9,Fown islands," said Kaushal, who is a
OL,10,Fsenior research fellow at the Royal
OL,11,FUnited Services Institute (RUSI).
OL,13,FIf troops were inserted onto the
OL,14,Fisland by helicopter or aircraft -
OL,15,Flikely to be a "major part of the
OL,16,Finitial phase", Kaushal said - the US
OL,17,Fwould also need to suppress Iran's
OL,18,Fdefensive missile systems through
OL,19,Fdrones, fighter jets or helicopters.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30409
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1774887078
OL,3,CHow could US forces seize Kharg Island
OL,4,Cand would Iran benefit?
OL,6,FHow would the US hold onto the island
OL,7,Fand could seizing it backfire?
OL,9,FExperts have warned maintaining
OL,10,Fcontrol of Kharg Island could be more
OL,11,Fdifficult than seizing it, with Trump
OL,12,Feven telling the Financial Times of
OL,13,Fany future attack: "It would also mean
OL,14,Fwe had to be there for a while."
OL,16,FThe island's close proximity to Iran's
OL,17,Fcoast could leave the US vulnerable to
OL,18,Fattack from the mainland, and
OL,19,Fsustaining that defence would likely
OL,20,Frequire air, land and sea power.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30410
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1774887078
OL,3,CHow could US forces seize Kharg Island
OL,4,Cand would Iran benefit?
OL,6,FIran's southern coastline is
OL,7,Fmountainous, and has a shelter network
OL,8,Fbuilt into it, providing plenty of
OL,9,Fplaces to hide UAV launchers,
OL,10,Fartillery and missiles, Kaushal said.
OL,12,FThe island's small size is also a
OL,13,Fdouble-edged sword, as it would makes
OL,14,Fany force on the ground easier to
OL,15,Flocate, fix, and pressure over time,
OL,16,Fsaid Dr Andreas Krieg, a senior
OL,17,Flecturer in Middle Eastern studies at
OL,18,FKings College London.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30411
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1774887078
OL,3,CHow could US forces seize Kharg Island
OL,4,Cand would Iran benefit?
OL,6,F"The danger is that a mission sold as
OL,7,Fa limited seizure turns quickly into a
OL,8,Fmuch larger force-protection and
OL,9,Fsuppression mission," Krieg told ITV
OL,10,FNews.
OL,12,F"From Iran's point of view, that is a
OL,13,Fbenefit: Tehran would gain a fixed
OL,14,Ftarget, a propaganda opportunity, and
OL,15,Fa way to tie down US naval and air
OL,16,Fassets in a narrow and dangerous
OL,17,Foperating environment while still
OL,18,Fthreatening the wider Gulf."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30412
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1774887078
OL,3,CHow could US forces seize Kharg Island
OL,4,Cand would Iran benefit?
OL,6,FExperts have also compared attacking
OL,7,FKharg Island to the Russian capture of
OL,8,FSnake Island, a tiny outcrop in the
OL,9,Fnorth-west Black Sea, seized on first
OL,10,Fday of its invasion of Ukraine.
OL,12,FRussian troops spent 126 days on the
OL,13,Fisland, 22 miles from Ukraine's coast,
OL,14,Fbefore eventually abandoning it after
OL,15,Fencountering rounds of artillery fire
OL,16,Fand missile strikes.
OL,18,FWhat defences does Iran ?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30413
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1774887078
OL,3,CHow could US forces seize Kharg Island
OL,4,Cand would Iran benefit?
OL,6,FKharg Island is sometimes referred to
OL,7,Fas "Forbidden Island" due to its
OL,8,Flayered military presence - but some
OL,9,Fof its defences have already been
OL,10,Ftargeted by the US.
OL,12,FThe US bombed Kharg Island during the
OL,13,Fsecond week of the war, and Iran's
OL,14,Fsemi-official Fars news agency said
OL,15,Fthe strikes damaged an air defence
OL,16,Ffacility, naval base, airport control
OL,17,Ftower, missile and mine storage, and
OL,18,Fhelicopter hangar belonging to an
OL,19,Foffshore oil company.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30414
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1774887078
OL,3,CHow could US forces seize Kharg Island
OL,4,Cand would Iran benefit?
OL,6,FIranian media says it has since
OL,7,Freinforced the island by moving in
OL,8,Fadditional personnel, adding air-
OL,9,Fdefence coverage, and placing traps
OL,10,Fand portable air-defence systems.
OL,12,FEven if some on-island systems were
OL,13,Fdegraded, Tehran could still support
OL,14,Fthe defence from the mainland through
OL,15,F"coastal missile coverage, drone
OL,16,Flaunches, small-boat activity,
OL,17,Felectronic interference, and rapid
OL,18,Freinforcement attempts", Krieg said.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G14/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30415
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1774887078
OL,3,CHow could US forces seize Kharg Island
OL,4,Cand would Iran benefit?
OL,6,F"Iran has a long-standing pattern of
OL,7,Fusing underground storage and
OL,8,Fdispersed coastal infrastructure to
OL,9,Fpreserve maritime-strike capability
OL,10,Fafter bombardment, which means an
OL,11,Foccupying force would have to worry
OL,12,Fnot just about what is visibly on
OL,13,FKharg, but about what can be brought
OL,14,Fto bear on Kharg from nearby coastal
OL,15,Fnetworks," he said.
OL,17,FWhat has Trump said?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G15/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30416
SC,0016
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1774887078
OL,3,CHow could US forces seize Kharg Island
OL,4,Cand would Iran benefit?
OL,6,FTrump has threatened to attack Kharg
OL,7,FIsland - along with other crucial
OL,8,Fenergy sites in Iran - if the two
OL,9,Fcountries do not reach a ceasefire
OL,10,Fdeal soon.
OL,12,F"The United States of America is in
OL,13,Fserious discussions with A NEW, AND
OL,14,FMORE REASONABLE, REGIME to end our
OL,15,FMilitary Operations in Iran," the
OL,16,Fpresident wrote on Truth Social on
OL,17,FMarch 30.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G16/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30417
SC,0017
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1774887078
OL,3,CHow could US forces seize Kharg Island
OL,4,Cand would Iran benefit?
OL,6,F"Great progress has been made but, if
OL,7,Ffor any reason a deal is not shortly
OL,8,Freached, which it probably will be,
OL,9,Fand if the Hormuz Strait is not
OL,10,Fimmediately 'Open for Business', we
OL,11,Fwill conclude our lovely 'stay' in
OL,12,FIran by blowing up and completely
OL,13,Fobliterating all of their Electric
OL,14,FGenerating Plants, Oil Wells and Kharg
OL,15,FIsland (and possibly all
OL,16,Fdesalinization plants!), which we have
OL,17,Fpurposefully not yet 'touched'."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G17/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30418
SC,0018
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1774887078
OL,3,CHow could US forces seize Kharg Island
OL,4,Cand would Iran benefit?
OL,6,FTrump had previously said his
OL,7,F"favourite" move would be to "take the
OL,8,Foil in Iran" during an interview with
OL,9,Fthe Financial Times, published late on
OL,10,FMarch 29.
OL,12,F"Maybe we take Kharg Island, maybe we
OL,13,Fdon't. We have a lot of options. It
OL,14,Fwould also mean we had to be there for
OL,15,Fa while," he said.
OL,17,FMultiple reports in US media last week
OL,18,Fsuggested senior White House officials
OL,19,Fwere considering a land invasion of
OL,20,Fthe island, as thousands of troops
OL,21,Fmade their way to the region.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G18/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
